        "author_association": "MEMBER",
        "body": "Imagine that once the nightlies show up, we will see more usage of them. Certainly RAPIDS is one use case that could benefit. When we added Conda packages, they also saw usage in Coiled. So imagine we might see similar usage emerge.\r\n\r\nSome use cases prefer wheels over installing from source ( https://github.com/zarr-developers/zarr-python/issues/1370 ), so those kinds of use cases would be easier to support if we had nightly wheels.\r\n\r\nSure we could imagine several ways we might distribute wheels. Here are some options:\r\n\r\n1. PyPI pre-releases (as you mentioned)\r\n2. Anaconda.org (as it also supports wheels)\r\n3. GitHub releases (or maybe GitHub packages if it supports it)\r\n\r\nProbably 1 or 2 is easiest since we already make use of those. Maybe 1 could dovetail into existing release processes. 2 would benefit from existing nightly build infra. There may be some benefits to 3 (if viable) as it could integrate well with GHA",
